<item ID="1774965071" Creator="Robert Hamrick" proto="Markdown" >
<attribute name="Created" >2026-03-31T06:51:10-07:00</attribute>
<attribute name="DominantLanguage" >en</attribute>
<attribute name="Height" >3</attribute>
<attribute name="Modified" >2026-04-05T05:24:43-07:00</attribute>
<attribute name="NLOrganizations" >ANN</attribute>
<attribute name="Name" >2.1 What is machine learning?</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiment" >-0.6521739273</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >-0.6;-0.6;-0.8;-0.4;-0.6;-0.8;-1;-0.6;-0.6;-0.8;-0.6;-0.8;-0.8;-0.8;-0.4;-0.8;-0.8;-0.8;-1;-0.6;-0.6;0.4;-0.6</attribute>
<attribute name="Width" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >50.5</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >* Artificial intelligence: machines performing human tasks
* Machine learning:   training models to make predictions
* Deep learning: transformer-based neural networks
* Generative AI: can create new content

AI ⊂ ML ⊂ Deep Learning ⊂ Generative AI

Machine learning is the study of algorithms and statistical models to perform a task using inference instead of instructions.
* spend a lot of time on training models

Deep learning:
* use artificial neural networks (ANN)
    * neurons have more than one input and a single output
     * activate output based on transformation of the inputs
* network is composed of layers of artificial neurons with connections between the layers
    * output of one neuron connects to inputs in the next layer.
    * input layer populated from training data
    * neurons activate in all layers until output is produced in the output layer
* accuracy of output is measured.  training is repeated if doesn’t meet threshold.  but with slight changes in connections between neurons.
* repeated: strengthen connections that lead to success, diminish connections that lead to failure.
* not much time on training models.  instead, model data with different ANN architectures

Generative AI:
* powered by very large ML models called Foundation Models (FM) that are pretrained on vast amounts of data.
* traditional ML models are single-task-oriented, FM can be used for different tasks without further training
* transformer architecture from deep learning made generative ai possible</text>
