<item ID="1774965136" Creator="Robert Hamrick" proto="Markdown" >
<attribute name="Created" >2026-03-31T06:52:15-07:00</attribute>
<attribute name="DominantLanguage" >en</attribute>
<attribute name="Height" >3</attribute>
<attribute name="Modified" >2026-04-06T04:53:15-07:00</attribute>
<attribute name="NLNames" >AMIs;Lex;Personalize;Polly;Seaborn</attribute>
<attribute name="NLOrganizations" >Amazon;Apache</attribute>
<attribute name="Name" >2.4 Machine learning tools overview</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiment" >-0.2300000042</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >-1;-0.4;-0.4;-0.4;-0.4;0.6;0.6;-0.2;0.6;-0.4;-0.6;0.2;-0.4;-0.6;-0.2;-0.2;0.4;0;0.2;0.4;-0.6;-0.2;-0.4;-0.4;0;-0.4;-0.4;-0.8;-1;-0.8;-0.8;-0.6;-0.2;-0.6;1;-0.6;0;-0.2;-0.6;0.6</attribute>
<attribute name="Width" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >61.5</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >Python tools
* Jupyter Notebook
* JupyterLab

Python Libraries
* pandas
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn
* NumPy
* scikit-learn

Frameworks
* PyTorch
* TensorFlow
* Keras
* Caffe2
* Gluon
* CNTK
* Torch
* Chainer
* Apache MXNet

Compute Instances
* EC2 P3 instances
* EC2 C5 and C5n instances
* AWS IoT Greengrass
* Amazon Elastic Inference

Pre-packaged AMIs with popular frameworks

Amazon SageMaker
* manages deployment of resources
    * deploy EC2 instances using Jupyter Notebooks and JupyterLabs
    * manages deployment of compute resources
    * only need to connect to Jupyter environment
* provides resources for labelling data, training models, and hosting trained models
* AWS market place provides ready-to-use model packages and algorithms

Managed ML services
* computer vision: Rekognition, Textract
* speech: Polly, Transcribe
* language: Comprehend, Translate
* chatbots: Lex
* forecasting: Forecast
* recommendations: Personalize


</text>
