<item ID="1774965159" Creator="Robert Hamrick" proto="Markdown" >
<attribute name="Created" >2026-03-31T06:52:38-07:00</attribute>
<attribute name="DominantLanguage" >en</attribute>
<attribute name="Height" >3</attribute>
<attribute name="Modified" >2026-04-06T05:09:48-07:00</attribute>
<attribute name="NLOrganizations" >Amazon</attribute>
<attribute name="Name" >Demo - Amazon SageMaker</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiment" >-0.2823529489</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >0.8;0.2;-0.6;-0.2;-0.8;0.8;-0.2;0.2;-0.6;-0.4;-0.4;-0.4;-1;-0.6;-0.4;-0.6;-0.6</attribute>
<attribute name="Width" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >72.5</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >In this course:
* use Jupyter Notebooks to prepare and process data
* write code to train models
* deploy models to SageMaker hosting
* test and validate models

Features: Ground Truth, Notebook, Training, Inference

Ground Truth: label datasets

Train model

Deploy model with inference pipeline

Find many pre-built models in AWS marketplace

Create a new Jupyter Notebook instance
* Notebook &gt; Notebook Instances &gt; Create notebook instance
* enter name, select instance type
* specify IAM role or create a new role
* create notebook instance
* open jupyter

</text>
