<item ID="1774965249" Creator="Robert Hamrick" proto="Markdown" >
<attribute name="Created" >2026-03-31T06:54:08-07:00</attribute>
<attribute name="DominantLanguage" >en</attribute>
<attribute name="Height" >3</attribute>
<attribute name="Modified" >2026-04-13T13:10:05-07:00</attribute>
<attribute name="Name" >3.3 Evaluating your data: describing your data; finding correlations</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiment" >-0.3117647114</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >-0.8;-0.8;-0.8;-0.8;-0.8;0.2;-0.6;-0.8;-0.4;-0.6;0.2;0.2;-0.8;-1;0.4;-1;0;0.2;0;-0.6;-0.4;-0.4;0;0.2;-0.2;-0.2;-0.6;-0.2;-0.4;-0.6;0.8;0.6;-0.8;0.2</attribute>
<attribute name="Width" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >61.5</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >* format data
* examine data types
* perform descriptive statistics
* visualize data

### Intro to Pandas dataframes

### Describe your data

Descriptive statistics
* overall statistics
    * number of rows, columns:  too many features?
* attribute statistics
    * sense of shape of attributes:  mean, std deviations, minimum, maximum valuables
    * mean: useful if data is symmetrical, but outliers skew
    * median:  not affected by outliers in the same way
* multivariate statistics
    * correlations between attributes:  closely correlated attributes lead to poor model performance

Categorical data:
* frequency of values and class imbalances?

Use histograms and box plots to answer questions about:
* range of the data
* peak
* outliers
* special features

Plotting multivariate statistics, to show relationship between variables:
* scatter plot 
* scatter plot matrix

### Finding correlations

How can you quantify the linear relationship among the variables you see in a scatter plot?

Try a correlation matrix to convey the strong and weak relationship between numerical variables.

Correlation is between -1 and 1.
* 1 =&gt; perfectly correlated:  y is proportional to x
* -1 =&gt; inverse:  y is proportional to -x
* 0 =&gt; no linear relationship (although it doesn’t mean that there is no relationship)

Heat map:  correlation=1 in green, correlation=-1 in brown
</text>
