<attribute name="Name" >Lab 3.6 - Amazon SageMaker - Generating model performance metrics</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >0.8;-0.2;0.2;0;0.6;-0.6;-0.8</attribute>
<attribute name="Width" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >94.5</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >In this lab, you will evaluate the model that you trained in previous labs and calculate metrics based on the results of the test data.

Objectives
After completing this lab, you will be able to:
* Use the test data to generate predictions
* Generate a confusion matrix from the results
* Generate performance metrics for the model
</text>
