<attribute name="Sentiments" >-0.6;-0.8;0;0.2;0.6;0.6</attribute>
<attribute name="Width" >5</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >94.5</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >In this lab, you will create a hyperparameter tuning job to tune the model that you created previously. You will then compare the metrics of the two models.

After completing this lab, you will be able to:
* Use Amazon SageMaker to create a hyperparameter training job
* Tune an XGBoost model by using Amazon SageMaker
* Test the tuned model by using performance metrics
</text>
