<attribute name="Xpos" >69.5</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >Shows variation and distance from the mean.  Useful for finding outliers.
```
df[&apos;degree_spondylolisthesis&apos;].plot.box()
```
Or to compare class 0 to class 1 for all columns:
```
df.groupby(&apos;class&apos;).boxplot(fontsize=20,rot=90,figsize=(20,10),patch_artist=True)
```</text>
