<attribute name="Name" >AWS Labs: Submission Change (Ignore &quot;Submit&quot; Button)</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiment" >-0.483333343</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >-1;-0.6;-0.8;-0.4;-0.6;-0.4;-0.2;-0.8;-0.8;-0.6;0;0.4</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >63</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >Posted Apr 10 6:30pm
AWS Labs: Submission Change (Ignore “Submit” Button)
Hi everyone,
A change of plan for how to submit your work for the labs in this class.  The &apos;Submit&apos; button there will not do anything, so here is the new process.
From here on:
	•	For some labs, upload a screenshot of key steps or outputs in Canvas.  I&apos;ll say exactly what to include.
	•	Other labs will not need any screenshots, and I can verify your work on the backend.  I&apos;ll be clear about which ones.
	•	This week, only Lab 3.1 needs a screenshot turned in.  I can verify 3.2 and 3.3 based on what is captured by the system.
	•	If you already finished Lab 3.1 and didn&apos;t take a screenshot, don&apos;t redo it.  I will grade it based on what I can see.
Reach out if you have questions.  Amazon sometimes will make changes like this mid-stream, so we’re adjusting as we go.
Prof. Amato
</text>
