<text >Posted Apr 7 4:30pm
Hi everyone!  We are heading into the second week of the class.  In this module we will look at formatting data for ML problems, how to load it into AWS and analyze it, and get introduced to how to use Jupyter notebooks for exploring.
Be sure to accept your invitation to the AWS Canvas system and login this week.  If you do not accept and enter the class by Friday, you may be dropped from the roster.  Earlier today I resent invites for those that have not yet accepted (it goes to your inSite email address).  If you would like me to use a different email, please let me know as soon as possible.
A quick note:  you may notice that AWS Module 3 has several parts.  We will be covering only the first half of the lecture and labs this week (Sections 1-4, Labs 3.1 - 3.3).  We will look at the second half next week.  For the labs, the &apos;Submit&apos; button is only needed for the first one (3.1).  There is nothing else to do after completing 3.2 and 3.3, your work is already captured by the end system.  You can take/retake these as many times as needed.  
See you online,
Prof. Amato
</text>
