<attribute name="NLOrganizations" >AWS Academy;AWS Academy Canvas;AWS SageMaker;Amazon AWS;Canvas</attribute>
<attribute name="NLPlaces" >Amato</attribute>
<attribute name="Name" >Welcome</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiment" >-0.2100000046</attribute>
<attribute name="Sentiments" >0.2;0.2;-0.2;0.4;-0.2;0.6;0.8;-0.4;-0.6;-0.6;-0.6;-1;-0.8;-0.6;0;-1;-0.6;-0.4;0.2;0.4</attribute>
<attribute name="Xpos" >54</attribute>
<attribute name="Ypos" >0</attribute>
<text >Welcome
Hello everyone, welcome back from spring break.  You should see this class (COMSC-178-5632) on your Canvas dashboard starting today.   To start, go to the Introduction module here and view the course overview video.
The course is divided into weekly modules that start on Tuesdays (except this week we will have an extra day, since we&apos;re starting on a Monday). 
The weekly routine is:
	•	Login to Canvas and check the new module posted.  It will have links to everything you need for the week.
	•	Complete the video, readings and hands-on lab with support from your professor and classmates.  The labs will start next week.
	•	We will have other activities from time to time such as group discussions.
Before you begin, please review the following information on background knowledge expectations:
	•	This class has advisory prerequisites for Python (COMSC-140) and the AWS Cloud platform (COMSC-175).
	•	You should have basic familiarity with the Python syntax.  You do not need expert-level skills in Python, but we will be using the language for our machine learning labs which will involve working with snippets of code.  If you have no programming experience or Python is unfamiliar to you, this class may be difficult to complete and I recommend starting with COMSC-140 instead.  We will not be writing Python programs but we will be using provided code snippets to accomplish tasks with data.
	•	The class uses several parts of the AWS platform such as AWS SageMaker.  If you are unfamiliar with AWS, this class will be extra challenging and you may not be able to complete all of the labs.  In this case I suggest starting with a different class such as COMSC-175.
If this is your first time taking an online course or would just like a refresher, I strongly recommend reviewing this page
Links to an external site.
 for online class procedures and help.
You should have received an email invite to join the AWS Academy Canvas platform.  This will go to the email address you have registered in InSite -- check your &apos;spam&apos; folder if you don&apos;t see it in your inbox.  
We will be using the official AWS Academy curriculum in this course.  This is also a Canvas system that you will use to access video and hands-on labs in the Amazon AWS cloud.  It is important to setup your account there during the first week.  If you did not receive an invite or something goes wrong please email me as soon as possible.  You can also post to the discussion forum topic here if you run into any problems.  Our class follows an 8-week schedule, so the pace will be a bit quicker and may feel faster than you&apos;re used to in a full-semester course.
Lastly, please take minute to update your profile (a picture helps us get to know you!) and review your general settings (notification preferences, etc.) under the &apos;Account&apos; section on the upper left.
Welcome to the class!
Prof. Amato
</text>
